    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Garments having a strap encircling the neck and supporting the front of the bodice, leaving shoulders and most of the back bare.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030201/National Museum of American History, Dictionary of Costume (n.d.)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>僅有遮住前胸的布片及可繞過頸部的吊帶的肚兜式服裝，穿著時會露出肩膀和大半的背部。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prenda que tiene una cinta rodeando el cuello y que sostiene la parte delantera del cuerpo, dejando los hombros y la mayor parte de la espalda al descubierto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lijfjes, met een band rondom de hals, die het voorstuk omhooghoudt, zodat de schouders en het grootste deel van de rug onbedekt blijven.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
